This paper deals with the problem of partitioning players into groups based on their preferences, which is a classic problem in game theory (cs.GT). The use of preferences and the calculation of coalition values suggest that this paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of partitioning players into groups can be viewed as a combinatorial optimization problem, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The study of coalition values and the determination of Pareto optimal assignments may also be relevant to social networks and computational social science (cs.SI). Finally, the use of optimization techniques and the analysis of complexity suggest that this paper may also be relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
